2
00:00:14.807 --> 00:00:16.267
I know you're scared.

3
00:00:16.350 --> 00:00:17.560
- but I'm...
- Scared?

4
00:00:17.643 --> 00:00:18.769
It's natural. When someone

5
00:00:18.853 --> 00:00:19.895
has an attempt
made on their life...

6
00:00:19.979 --> 00:00:21.313
You know I was recruited

7
00:00:21.397 --> 00:00:23.649
by the FBI
and Central Intelligence?

8
00:00:23.733 --> 00:00:25.860
Scored a 99th percentile in IQ.

9
00:00:25.943 --> 00:00:27.486
but only an 80%
on the psych eval.

10
00:00:27.570 --> 00:00:30.906
You want to know why.
you condescending asshole?

11
00:00:30.990 --> 00:00:33.784
Interpersonal skills?

12
00:00:33.868 --> 00:00:37.913
I lack the ability
to tolerate horseshit.

13
00:00:37.997 --> 00:00:40.332
And this...

14
00:00:40.416 --> 00:00:43.085
and this... is horseshit!

15
00:00:43.169 --> 00:00:45.755
You think I'm some poor.
scared. little girl?

16
00:00:45.838 --> 00:00:47.590
I'm not scared. I am pissed.

17
00:00:47.673 --> 00:00:48.799
They came into my house

18
00:00:48.883 --> 00:00:50.551
that I fixed up with my money

19
00:00:50.634 --> 00:00:51.886
in the town
that my family founded

20
00:00:51.969 --> 00:00:53.387
because they think
they are untouchable.

21
00:00:57.016 --> 00:00:58.309
You want a gun?

22
00:00:58.392 --> 00:01:00.561
Uh-huh.

23
00:01:01.604 --> 00:01:03.105
Fine by me.

24
00:01:11.697 --> 00:01:13.657
Gray gave this to me
a couple of years ago.

25
00:01:13.741 --> 00:01:15.785
Wanted to keep it in the family.

26
00:01:15.868 --> 00:01:17.161
and I was
the only family he had.

27
00:01:18.162 --> 00:01:20.414
Not what you'd call
a subtle weapon.

28
00:01:22.583 --> 00:01:24.335
People round here
know I have this thing.

29
00:01:24.418 --> 00:01:26.086
Use it wrong.
and it gets back to me.

30
00:01:28.881 --> 00:01:31.008
So don't use it wrong.

31
00:01:31.091 --> 00:01:34.178
I won't let
anything happen to it.

32
00:01:49.443 --> 00:01:52.071
Your house isn't safe anymore;
pack your bags.

33
00:01:57.743 --> 00:01:59.328
Finlay?

34
00:01:59.411 --> 00:02:01.330
Got an ID on the body
that was found with Joe.

35
00:02:01.413 --> 00:02:02.957
We gotta get to the morgue.

36
00:02:14.802 --> 00:02:16.095
Are you kiddin' me?

37
00:02:16.178 --> 00:02:18.472
I just told you to be careful
with that thing.

38
00:02:18.556 --> 00:02:21.225
Never trust a weapon you
haven't personally test-fired.

39
00:02:48.252 --> 00:02:50.087
You two were already
working the case?

40
00:02:50.170 --> 00:02:51.213
First thing in the morning?

41
00:02:51.297 --> 00:02:53.090
We were just getting
back into town.

42
00:02:53.173 --> 00:02:54.550
From where?

43
00:02:54.633 --> 00:02:58.846
Alabama. Bar closed late.
storm flooded the road.

44
00:02:58.929 --> 00:03:01.432
You took him out drinking?

45
00:03:01.515 --> 00:03:03.893
Isn't that the exact opposite
of what I told you to do?

46
00:03:03.976 --> 00:03:05.352
Good thing I did.

47
00:03:05.436 --> 00:03:07.229
Whoever killed the Morrisons
came after us last night.

48
00:03:07.313 --> 00:03:09.315
Broke into my house.
carved a threat into my door;

49
00:03:09.398 --> 00:03:11.191
who knows what they would've
done if I'd been there alone.

50
00:03:11.275 --> 00:03:13.027
They came into your house?

51
00:03:14.069 --> 00:03:15.696
I'm fine.

52
00:03:15.779 --> 00:03:17.990
Let's just see
what Jasper has for us.

53
00:03:18.073 --> 00:03:19.992
It's okay.

54
00:03:20.075 --> 00:03:22.244
I had my eye on her.

55
00:03:26.707 --> 00:03:28.876
Here you go.
Here you go.

56
00:03:28.959 --> 00:03:31.253
Sorry; I didn't know
you were coming.

57
00:03:31.337 --> 00:03:33.547
Once the prints came back.
we got a full run on the man.

58
00:03:33.631 --> 00:03:35.925
Victim's name is Pete Jobling.

59
00:03:36.008 --> 00:03:38.636
Trucker for Southfreight
Shipping. which makes sense.

60
00:03:38.719 --> 00:03:40.262
'cause the test results
I got back

61
00:03:40.346 --> 00:03:41.805
showed a little too much
hydrogen sulfide

62
00:03:41.889 --> 00:03:43.515
in his blood gases and tissue;

63
00:03:43.599 --> 00:03:45.225
he spent his whole life
on the road.

64
00:03:45.309 --> 00:03:47.019
sniffing other people's
catalytic converters.

65
00:03:47.102 --> 00:03:49.647
43. married.
resides in Atlanta...

66
00:03:49.730 --> 00:03:51.565
Record's clean
except for a 2018 arrest

67
00:03:51.649 --> 00:03:53.442
for a Jacksonville
traffic violation

68
00:03:53.525 --> 00:03:55.110
that turned into
a disorderly conduct.

69
00:03:55.194 --> 00:03:58.739
Defended by Zacarias
Perez LLP. No conviction.

70
00:03:58.822 --> 00:04:00.282
Zacarias Perez. Here he is.

71
00:04:00.366 --> 00:04:02.701
Oh. Looks fancy.

72
00:04:02.785 --> 00:04:05.120
Not the kind of firm
that defends truck drivers.

73
00:04:05.204 --> 00:04:06.830
Thanks. Jasper.

74
00:04:06.914 --> 00:04:09.124
Hopefully we don't need
to see you again any time soon.

75
00:04:09.166 --> 00:04:10.709
Yeah.

76
00:04:12.878 --> 00:04:15.339
It's a D.C. number.

77
00:04:15.422 --> 00:04:17.466
- Secret Service.
- Hello?

78
00:04:17.549 --> 00:04:19.051
Officer Conklin?

79
00:04:19.134 --> 00:04:20.552
This is Molly Beth Gordon.

80
00:04:20.636 --> 00:04:22.930
Specialized Administrative
Officer with the Secret Service.

81
00:04:23.013 --> 00:04:24.431
I got your message
regarding Joe Reacher.

82
00:04:24.515 --> 00:04:25.474
I work with him.

83
00:04:25.557 --> 00:04:26.600
Uh. hi. Molly Beth.

84
00:04:26.684 --> 00:04:28.519
Oh. Joe!

85
00:04:28.602 --> 00:04:30.771
Oh. thank God.
Why haven't you

86
00:04:30.854 --> 00:04:32.481
returned my calls?
I was so worried.

87
00:04:35.567 --> 00:04:38.487
Ms. Gordon.
this is Jack Reacher.

88
00:04:38.570 --> 00:04:41.156
Joe's brother.

89
00:04:41.240 --> 00:04:42.992
Joe's dead.

90
00:04:44.243 --> 00:04:46.787
No.

91
00:04:46.870 --> 00:04:48.580
No. you're wrong.

92
00:04:48.664 --> 00:04:50.124
I'm not.

93
00:04:52.334 --> 00:04:53.794
How?

94
00:04:55.587 --> 00:04:57.089
He was murdered.

95
00:04:57.172 --> 00:05:00.009
We think his death
may be related to his work.

96
00:05:00.092 --> 00:05:01.969
Do you know what Joe was doing
in Margrave. Georgia?

97
00:05:02.052 --> 00:05:04.179
Uh... I don't know.

98
00:05:04.263 --> 00:05:05.931
He was. um...

99
00:05:06.015 --> 00:05:08.058
He was running
a classified investigation.

100
00:05:08.142 --> 00:05:10.811
I just don't know the details...

101
00:05:10.894 --> 00:05:11.937
God.

102
00:05:18.152 --> 00:05:20.404
I know it's not the best time
to answer questions.

103
00:05:20.487 --> 00:05:22.281
but we really need your help.

104
00:05:22.364 --> 00:05:25.075
What position did Joe hold
in the Secret Service?

105
00:05:25.159 --> 00:05:26.410
What? He was...

106
00:05:26.493 --> 00:05:28.495
Uh. he was. he was the.
he was the director.

107
00:05:28.579 --> 00:05:31.290
he was the director of
the Office of Investigations.

108
00:05:31.373 --> 00:05:33.208
You... you didn't know that?

109
00:05:35.127 --> 00:05:36.670
No.

110
00:05:36.754 --> 00:05:38.630
We hadn't spoken in a while.

111
00:05:38.714 --> 00:05:40.382
Was anyone working under him?

112
00:05:40.466 --> 00:05:42.051
No.

113
00:05:42.134 --> 00:05:44.553
No. um...

114
00:05:44.636 --> 00:05:46.764
No. he assigned
his current case to himself.

115
00:05:46.847 --> 00:05:48.015
Nobody knew about it.

116
00:05:48.098 --> 00:05:49.349
You did.

117
00:05:50.851 --> 00:05:52.853
We were close.

118
00:05:52.936 --> 00:05:55.856
Molly Beth. um.
this is Officer Conklin.

119
00:05:55.939 --> 00:05:58.025
I'm-I'm sorry.
we're almost done. I promise.

120
00:05:58.108 --> 00:06:00.402
Was there a specific
division of O.I.

121
00:06:00.486 --> 00:06:01.987
that Joe was heading up?

122
00:06:02.071 --> 00:06:04.531
Uh. yeah. he-he runs...

123
00:06:04.615 --> 00:06:07.576
he ran our
anti-counterfeiting department.

124
00:06:10.954 --> 00:06:12.414
Agent Gordon?

125
00:06:12.498 --> 00:06:15.250
Captain Finlay.
Chief Detective. Margrave PD.

126
00:06:15.334 --> 00:06:16.585
Had there been reports

127
00:06:16.668 --> 00:06:17.878
of counterfeiting
in the Margrave area?

128
00:06:17.961 --> 00:06:19.630
I... I really don't feel like...

129
00:06:19.713 --> 00:06:21.423
Can we just talk about this
another time. please?

130
00:06:21.507 --> 00:06:23.801
I know it's hard.
and I hate doing this.

131
00:06:23.884 --> 00:06:25.844
considering
what we just told you.

132
00:06:25.928 --> 00:06:27.554
but you're our only lead.

133
00:06:27.638 --> 00:06:30.516
On a case it appears
Joe died for.

134
00:06:30.599 --> 00:06:32.643
Um... Okay.

135
00:06:35.062 --> 00:06:37.648
Joe told me that he put a stop

136
00:06:37.731 --> 00:06:41.652
to all domestic counterfeiting
a while ago. Um...

137
00:06:41.735 --> 00:06:43.320
He put all
these procedures in place;

138
00:06:43.403 --> 00:06:44.780
made it basically impossible

139
00:06:44.863 --> 00:06:46.406
to make anything here
without getting caught.

140
00:06:46.490 --> 00:06:49.076
He was chasing
international stuff.

141
00:06:49.159 --> 00:06:50.077
Like South America?

142
00:06:50.160 --> 00:06:53.372
I don't know. Um...

143
00:06:53.455 --> 00:06:55.332
I can try to get
his files for you.

144
00:06:55.415 --> 00:06:56.416
Thank you.

145
00:06:56.500 --> 00:06:57.876
But hard copies only;

146
00:06:57.960 --> 00:06:59.670
we don't want a digital trail.

147
00:06:59.753 --> 00:07:01.380
Why?

148
00:07:01.463 --> 00:07:03.340
Seems whatever Joe was into.
people were killed over it.

149
00:07:03.423 --> 00:07:05.259
We don't want anything
leading back to you.

150
00:07:05.342 --> 00:07:06.635
We need to keep this quiet.

151
00:07:06.718 --> 00:07:08.512
Shouldn't I tell his superiors?

152
00:07:08.595 --> 00:07:09.847
Absolutely not.

153
00:07:09.930 --> 00:07:12.391
We can't trust
the Secret Service?

154
00:07:12.474 --> 00:07:15.269
Joe kept this top secret
for a reason.

155
00:07:15.352 --> 00:07:17.729
I believe in my brother's
instincts. Do you?

156
00:07:17.813 --> 00:07:19.898
- Yes.
- Okay. good.

157
00:07:19.982 --> 00:07:21.608
So we tell no one until
we have a better understanding

158
00:07:21.692 --> 00:07:23.235
of what we're dealing with.

159
00:07:23.318 --> 00:07:24.778
Okay. Um...

160
00:07:24.862 --> 00:07:27.531
it'll take me a day or so
to copy it all.

161
00:07:27.614 --> 00:07:29.158
That's okay.

162
00:07:31.618 --> 00:07:33.412
You sound just like him.

163
00:07:36.832 --> 00:07:38.417
We'll talk soon.

164
00:07:42.546 --> 00:07:44.840
Your counterfeiting guess
was right. Reacher.

165
00:07:44.923 --> 00:07:47.009
My bet was guns
or sex trafficking.

166
00:07:47.092 --> 00:07:49.136
Well. like you said.
everything comes down to cash.

167
00:07:49.219 --> 00:07:51.180
Counterfeiters just cut
out the middle man.

168
00:07:51.263 --> 00:07:53.974
But multiple murders
over Monopoly money?

169
00:07:54.057 --> 00:07:55.809
People kill over 20 bucks
in a wallet.

170
00:07:55.893 --> 00:07:57.686
Imagine what they'd do
to protect a limitless supply.

171
00:07:57.769 --> 00:07:59.771
We don't have to imagine; we've
been to the Morrisons' house.

172
00:07:59.855 --> 00:08:02.441
No way it's a coincidence
Hubble was a currency manager

173
00:08:02.524 --> 00:08:04.276
for Axis Financial's
Atlanta branch.

174
00:08:04.359 --> 00:08:05.527
Okay. so we check out
where he worked.

175
00:08:05.611 --> 00:08:07.529
I go there midday
flashing a badge.

176
00:08:07.613 --> 00:08:09.156
people clam up and lawyer up.

177
00:08:09.239 --> 00:08:11.074
I'll track down
some of the suits after hours.

178
00:08:11.158 --> 00:08:12.534
- Mm.
- But right now.

179
00:08:12.618 --> 00:08:14.411
I need you back in uniform
and at the station house.

180
00:08:14.494 --> 00:08:16.914
Pretend to look for the ex-cons
who killed the Morrisons.

181
00:08:16.997 --> 00:08:18.707
I'm sorry. what?

182
00:08:18.790 --> 00:08:20.334
Teale doesn't know
we suspect him.

183
00:08:20.417 --> 00:08:21.752
so we play his game for now.

184
00:08:21.835 --> 00:08:23.462
I'll tell him you found
your house broken into

185
00:08:23.545 --> 00:08:25.130
and you're determined
to find out who's responsible.

186
00:08:25.214 --> 00:08:27.299
So I get to watch Teale waving
his cane like a scepter.

187
00:08:27.382 --> 00:08:28.842
playin' boss;
what do you get to do?

188
00:08:28.926 --> 00:08:31.136
I'm going to pay a visit
to that jail guard. Spivey.

189
00:08:31.220 --> 00:08:33.055
Got his address this morning.
Next county over.

190
00:08:33.138 --> 00:08:34.139
I'll come.

191
00:08:34.223 --> 00:08:36.266
'Cause it went so well
the last time?

192
00:08:36.350 --> 00:08:39.102
No. you're gonna to go see
Zacarias Perez LLP.

193
00:08:39.186 --> 00:08:41.104
See what you can find out
about Jobling's arrest.

194
00:08:41.188 --> 00:08:42.731
An assignment?

195
00:08:42.814 --> 00:08:44.107
I thought I was not...

196
00:08:44.191 --> 00:08:45.609
By employment. appearance.
or lifestyle choice...

197
00:08:45.692 --> 00:08:46.693
A cop anymore.

198
00:08:46.777 --> 00:08:48.987
Well. shows you
how desperate I am.

199
00:08:49.071 --> 00:08:51.073
So be smart.
don't break the law.

200
00:08:51.156 --> 00:08:54.076
and promise me you won't
end up in another holding cell.

201
00:08:55.452 --> 00:08:56.954
No.

202
00:08:58.664 --> 00:09:01.250
Can't wait till this is over
and that guy's out of our town.

203
00:09:07.256 --> 00:09:09.007
Officer Conklin.

204
00:09:10.300 --> 00:09:11.885
Keeping banker's hours?

205
00:09:11.969 --> 00:09:13.428
I was at the morgue.

206
00:09:13.512 --> 00:09:15.222
getting intel
on the second highway victim.

207
00:09:15.305 --> 00:09:17.849
I made my directive clear.

208
00:09:17.933 --> 00:09:19.768
Those bodies take a backseat

209
00:09:19.851 --> 00:09:21.770
to those of our departed
colleague and his wife.

210
00:09:21.853 --> 00:09:23.897
A cop is dead.

211
00:09:23.981 --> 00:09:25.190
and from what I've heard.
we could've had another.

212
00:09:25.274 --> 00:09:26.358
You holdin' up all right?

213
00:09:26.441 --> 00:09:28.443
Yes. sir.

214
00:09:28.527 --> 00:09:30.279
Though if I had been home.
I would've taken

215
00:09:30.362 --> 00:09:31.905
at least a couple
of those bastards with me.

216
00:09:31.989 --> 00:09:33.532
That's the spirit. kid.

217
00:09:33.615 --> 00:09:35.993
If someone wants to come
after Margrave's finest.

218
00:09:36.076 --> 00:09:37.536
they better be ready
for a fight.

219
00:09:37.619 --> 00:09:40.247
Now. I want you focused on
these boys up on the board:

220
00:09:40.330 --> 00:09:43.917
some of the more violent perps
Morrison helped incarcerate.

221
00:09:44.001 --> 00:09:45.877
Aggravated battery.

222
00:09:45.961 --> 00:09:48.046
domestic assault.

223
00:09:48.130 --> 00:09:50.549
armed robbery.
Bad men.

224
00:09:50.632 --> 00:09:52.175
Copy that.

225
00:09:52.259 --> 00:09:53.885
I'm in the process
of running down

226
00:09:53.969 --> 00:09:55.554
stolen car reports
for the whole county.

227
00:09:55.637 --> 00:09:57.097
Figure if an ex-con was gonna

228
00:09:57.180 --> 00:09:58.432
go to a cop's house.
he wouldn't risk

229
00:09:58.515 --> 00:09:59.766
using his own ride.

230
00:09:59.850 --> 00:10:01.143
Well. that's good thinkin'.

231
00:10:01.226 --> 00:10:02.894
You keep me posted.

232
00:10:02.978 --> 00:10:04.313
Hmm.

233
00:10:14.865 --> 00:10:16.241
Roscoe?

234
00:10:17.451 --> 00:10:18.660
You were with
Finlay this morning?

235
00:10:18.744 --> 00:10:20.329
I was.

236
00:10:20.412 --> 00:10:23.498
And. uh...
someone came after you?

237
00:10:23.582 --> 00:10:24.958
Appears that way.

238
00:10:25.042 --> 00:10:26.335
Could be related to Morrison.

239
00:10:26.418 --> 00:10:27.961
could be teens with
a fucked-up sense of humor.

240
00:10:28.045 --> 00:10:30.589
Yeah. Um...

241
00:10:30.672 --> 00:10:33.675
My cousin Charlie's
not picking up her phone.

242
00:10:33.759 --> 00:10:36.428
Paul. either.
The whole family's disappeared.

243
00:10:36.511 --> 00:10:39.181
Just wondering if you know
something I don't.

244
00:10:39.264 --> 00:10:41.808
No.

245
00:10:41.892 --> 00:10:43.143
Do you?

246
00:10:43.226 --> 00:10:45.270
Nope. I'm just trying

247
00:10:45.354 --> 00:10:47.022
to figure out what the hell's
going on around here.

248
00:10:47.105 --> 00:10:48.940
Yeah. Me. too.

249
00:10:49.024 --> 00:10:51.693
I haven't had any luck.
so I'm just gonna

250
00:10:51.777 --> 00:10:54.446
focus on the ex-cons.
like Teale said.

251
00:10:54.529 --> 00:10:56.531
You really think
that's the way to go on this?

252
00:10:56.615 --> 00:10:59.242
Good a road as any.

253
00:10:59.326 --> 00:11:01.119
Teale's boss now.

254
00:11:03.413 --> 00:11:05.082
What about Finlay?

255
00:11:05.165 --> 00:11:06.833
Think he might know something
he ain't sharing?

256
00:11:06.917 --> 00:11:08.502
I doubt it.

257
00:11:08.585 --> 00:11:11.254
Everybody in Margrave still
treats him like the new guy.

258
00:11:11.338 --> 00:11:15.384
Yeah. Well. whole town's wound
tighter than jungle gym screws.

259
00:11:15.467 --> 00:11:18.261
I don't know what
to tell my wife.

260
00:11:18.345 --> 00:11:20.555
This Reacher guy's
running all over everybody

261
00:11:20.639 --> 00:11:22.182
- like it's...
- Stevenson?

262
00:11:22.265 --> 00:11:23.934
A moment.

263
00:11:24.017 --> 00:11:25.894
Yes. sir.

264
00:12:09.020 --> 00:12:10.605
Mr. Spivey?

265
00:12:14.443 --> 00:12:16.278
Tanner Spivey?

266
00:12:29.291 --> 00:12:31.334
Mr. Spivey?

267
00:13:31.353 --> 00:13:32.687
Alton police!

268
00:13:33.939 --> 00:13:36.024
- You picked the wrong town to rob in.
- Wait!

269
00:13:38.777 --> 00:13:40.570
Those bruises look pretty fresh.

270
00:13:40.654 --> 00:13:41.988
You still feelin' 'em?

271
00:13:42.072 --> 00:13:43.532
A bit.

272
00:13:45.075 --> 00:13:47.327
The accident was
just a few days ago.

273
00:13:49.913 --> 00:13:53.625
Well. truth be told.
Mr. Doyle...

274
00:13:53.708 --> 00:13:56.253
I'm sorry. what was your
first name again?

275
00:13:56.336 --> 00:13:58.672
Uh. Brian.

276
00:13:58.755 --> 00:14:00.465
Truth be told. Brian.

277
00:14:00.549 --> 00:14:02.842
we don't normally handle
auto claims here.

278
00:14:02.926 --> 00:14:04.678
Usually leave that to
the bus bench crowd.

279
00:14:04.761 --> 00:14:07.597
But The Home Depot's
got deep pockets

280
00:14:07.681 --> 00:14:10.892
and I intend to get my hands
all the way in 'em.

281
00:14:10.976 --> 00:14:13.270
get you the recovery
you deserve.

282
00:14:13.353 --> 00:14:15.730
So. let's start
at the beginning.

283
00:14:15.814 --> 00:14:18.400
What was the date
that delivery truck hit you?

284
00:14:18.483 --> 00:14:20.193
There was no truck.

285
00:14:20.277 --> 00:14:22.571
I made up a story
so you'd see me.

286
00:14:22.654 --> 00:14:24.197
Now get me your file
on Pete Jobling.

287
00:14:25.407 --> 00:14:26.491
Excuse me?

288
00:14:26.575 --> 00:14:28.952
A client you represented
for a traffic violation

289
00:14:29.035 --> 00:14:31.162
and disorderly conduct charge.

290
00:14:31.246 --> 00:14:32.831
His file.

291
00:14:32.914 --> 00:14:34.416
Get it.

292
00:14:34.499 --> 00:14:36.793
I don't know what game
you're playing at here.

293
00:14:36.876 --> 00:14:38.503
but get out of my office.

294
00:14:38.587 --> 00:14:40.088
No.

295
00:14:40.171 --> 00:14:41.464
Excuse me?

296
00:14:41.548 --> 00:14:43.174
Who the hell
do you think you are?

297
00:14:43.258 --> 00:14:45.594
A pissed-off drifter
with nothing to lose.

298
00:14:45.677 --> 00:14:47.345
Oh. you want to get arrested
for trespassing?

299
00:14:47.429 --> 00:14:49.097
Pull up Jobling's file. Now.

300
00:14:49.180 --> 00:14:52.976
I will ruin your life
with one phone call.

301
00:14:53.059 --> 00:14:55.353
I'll end your life
with one phone.

302
00:15:02.193 --> 00:15:03.612
Pull up Jobling's file.

303
00:15:07.365 --> 00:15:08.867
Print it.

304
00:15:11.786 --> 00:15:13.038
Staple.

305
00:15:14.664 --> 00:15:15.999
Little further.

306
00:15:17.125 --> 00:15:18.335
Here you go.

307
00:15:22.005 --> 00:15:23.757
Thank you.

308
00:15:26.301 --> 00:15:27.927
Oh.

309
00:15:28.011 --> 00:15:30.096
Don't bother trying
to find out my real name.

310
00:15:30.180 --> 00:15:31.723
Cause any problems.

311
00:15:31.806 --> 00:15:33.642
you'll wish
I'd finished strangling you.

312
00:15:47.530 --> 00:15:51.326
Listen. man. you should've
told us you were a cop.

313
00:15:52.369 --> 00:15:54.329
Hard to do
with a boot in your mouth.

314
00:16:08.885 --> 00:16:11.012
And it shouldn't make
a difference.

315
00:16:20.730 --> 00:16:22.357
Jesus.

316
00:16:23.483 --> 00:16:25.110
Which one of you assholes
did this?

317
00:16:25.193 --> 00:16:27.153
Thought he was a burglar.

318
00:16:27.237 --> 00:16:29.614
How many burglars you know
wear suits?

319
00:16:29.698 --> 00:16:31.366
He didn't look
like he lived there.

320
00:16:31.449 --> 00:16:33.743
- Are you fuckin' kidding me right now?
- Hey.

321
00:16:33.827 --> 00:16:35.120
Let it go.

322
00:16:35.203 --> 00:16:36.579
We have bigger fights.

323
00:16:36.663 --> 00:16:39.874
Come on. Come on.

324
00:16:39.958 --> 00:16:42.127
Come on.

325
00:16:46.673 --> 00:16:48.508
You know. cursing is
a sign of a weak mind

326
00:16:48.591 --> 00:16:51.094
and a weaker character.

327
00:16:51.177 --> 00:16:54.139
But I appreciate
you having my back.

328
00:16:54.222 --> 00:16:55.640
Of course.

329
00:16:55.724 --> 00:16:57.767
You hear from Reacher?

330
00:16:57.851 --> 00:16:59.519
We're meeting him at Jolene's.

331
00:16:59.602 --> 00:17:00.645
Said he found something.

332
00:17:00.729 --> 00:17:03.314
Good. 'Cause so did I.

333
00:17:21.875 --> 00:17:23.585
Cops or civilians?

334
00:17:23.668 --> 00:17:25.920
Just Southern hospitality.

335
00:17:26.004 --> 00:17:28.256
How'd it go at the law firm?

336
00:17:28.339 --> 00:17:30.091
Got everything I needed.

337
00:17:30.175 --> 00:17:31.217
How?

338
00:17:31.301 --> 00:17:34.387
Just... used the phone.

339
00:17:36.055 --> 00:17:39.017
Two fried chicken thighs.
fried okra. ribs.

340
00:17:39.100 --> 00:17:41.978
collard greens. pole beans.
rice with giblet gravy.

341
00:17:42.061 --> 00:17:43.229
cottage cheese and peaches.

342
00:17:43.313 --> 00:17:45.982
Buttermilk chicken sandwich
with coleslaw.

343
00:17:46.065 --> 00:17:49.611
And for you. spinach salad.
Dressing on the side.

344
00:17:49.694 --> 00:17:51.821
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

345
00:17:51.905 --> 00:17:53.907
I was embarrassed ordering that.

346
00:17:53.990 --> 00:17:56.451
How do you eat like that
and still look like you do?

347
00:17:56.534 --> 00:17:58.453
Like this.

348
00:18:02.290 --> 00:18:04.042
So. Roscoe says
you found something.

349
00:18:06.252 --> 00:18:08.713
Our dead trucker's employer.
Southfreight Shipping?

350
00:18:08.797 --> 00:18:10.965
They were contracted to
Kliner Industries.

351
00:18:11.049 --> 00:18:13.301
When our trucker got into
legal trouble.

352
00:18:13.384 --> 00:18:15.261
Kliner paid his legal fees.

353
00:18:15.345 --> 00:18:17.222
That makes what I came across
even more interesting.

354
00:18:17.305 --> 00:18:19.224
- What's that?
- I searched Spivey's house.

355
00:18:19.307 --> 00:18:21.226
Looks like he left town.

356
00:18:21.309 --> 00:18:23.645
But his landline showed multiple
calls to Kliner Industries.

357
00:18:23.728 --> 00:18:25.688
So. roads are leading to Kliner.

358
00:18:25.772 --> 00:18:27.273
The patron saint of Margrave?

359
00:18:27.357 --> 00:18:29.025
You really think that
he could be counterfeiting?

360
00:18:29.108 --> 00:18:31.611
Who knows? He certainly has
the financial resources

361
00:18:31.694 --> 00:18:32.987
to pull off something
of this scale.

362
00:18:33.071 --> 00:18:34.739
Maybe he has those resources

363
00:18:34.823 --> 00:18:37.367
- because he's counterfeiting.
- Mm.

364
00:18:37.450 --> 00:18:39.077
Well. how does Hubble's
bank fit into all this?

365
00:18:39.160 --> 00:18:42.372
Not sure. But I'm gonna break
into Kliner's tonight

366
00:18:42.455 --> 00:18:44.123
and see if I can find something
that connects them.

367
00:18:44.207 --> 00:18:46.084
You can't just sit there
and say you're gonna violate

368
00:18:46.167 --> 00:18:48.294
the Fourth Amendment
while you eat okra.

369
00:18:48.378 --> 00:18:49.879
Yes. I can.

370
00:18:49.963 --> 00:18:52.465
- Wanna see me do it again?
- Reacher...

371
00:18:52.549 --> 00:18:54.717
I don't know what we'll find
or not find.

372
00:18:54.801 --> 00:18:56.886
Things maybe lead to Kliner.

373
00:18:56.970 --> 00:18:58.096
We're flying blind here.

374
00:18:58.179 --> 00:18:59.931
so somebody's gotta kick
the hornet's nest.

375
00:19:00.014 --> 00:19:01.766
You jeopardize this
investigation

376
00:19:01.850 --> 00:19:03.476
if you get evidence
that's inadmissible

377
00:19:03.560 --> 00:19:05.645
because it was
unlawfully obtained.

378
00:19:05.728 --> 00:19:08.356
You get that busted nose
filling out a warrant

379
00:19:08.439 --> 00:19:09.899
to search Spivey's house?

380
00:19:09.983 --> 00:19:12.193
A man who may have information
regarding a murder

381
00:19:12.277 --> 00:19:13.653
had disappeared.

382
00:19:13.736 --> 00:19:14.696
He didn't return my calls.

383
00:19:14.779 --> 00:19:15.947
so I went to his house.

384
00:19:16.030 --> 00:19:18.825
No answer there. despite
it being mid-afternoon.

385
00:19:18.908 --> 00:19:20.827
and he not reporting to work
that day.

386
00:19:20.910 --> 00:19:23.830
I had a reasonable belief
that Spivey could be in danger.

387
00:19:23.913 --> 00:19:26.499
- Mm.
- Exigent circumstances are exceptions

388
00:19:26.583 --> 00:19:27.709
to the warrant requirement.

389
00:19:27.792 --> 00:19:30.920
Exigent circumstances?
That's bullshit.

390
00:19:31.004 --> 00:19:33.464
Maybe. But it's legal.

391
00:19:33.548 --> 00:19:35.133
Okay. fine.

392
00:19:35.216 --> 00:19:36.968
I won't break into
Kliner's office.

393
00:19:37.051 --> 00:19:39.345
I'll walk in
and talk to him. Now.

394
00:19:39.429 --> 00:19:41.389
I'm coming.
A man that powerful.

395
00:19:41.472 --> 00:19:43.182
someone's gotta keep
a cool head.

396
00:19:43.266 --> 00:19:45.560
Okay. I think
I know what's going on here.

397
00:19:45.643 --> 00:19:47.687
but if you two can't play nice.
I'm gonna do what Meemaw used to

398
00:19:47.770 --> 00:19:50.064
and make you sit on the ground
and hold hands.

399
00:19:52.358 --> 00:19:55.695
Okay... eat it or clean it up.

400
00:19:55.778 --> 00:19:57.739
Jolene's not your mama.

401
00:20:00.033 --> 00:20:03.244
I gotta go keep tracking down
those rental cars. Bye.

402
00:20:08.124 --> 00:20:10.084
I'm taking those ribs to go.

403
00:20:16.049 --> 00:20:18.885
You hungry?

404
00:20:18.968 --> 00:20:20.762
Good boy.

405
00:20:21.804 --> 00:20:23.723
Reacher. what are you doin'?

406
00:20:23.806 --> 00:20:27.852
Owner's been leaving him out.
not giving him water.

407
00:20:27.936 --> 00:20:31.022
What the hell's goin' on here?

408
00:20:31.105 --> 00:20:33.066
This your dog. sir?

409
00:20:33.149 --> 00:20:36.194
It was my uncle's.
He died a few weeks ago.

410
00:20:36.277 --> 00:20:38.363
I didn't want the mutt.
but now I got it.

411
00:20:38.446 --> 00:20:41.115
"It"? What's his name?

412
00:20:41.199 --> 00:20:42.784
It was a barn dog.
Got no name.

413
00:20:42.867 --> 00:20:45.787
Now. I told you the other day
to stay the hell out of my yard.

414
00:20:45.870 --> 00:20:48.373
Negligent care of an animal's
a misdemeanor in Margrave.

415
00:20:48.456 --> 00:20:50.917
$500 fine.
up to ten days in jail.

416
00:20:51.000 --> 00:20:52.835
Everything going on
in this town.

417
00:20:52.919 --> 00:20:54.754
and you're worried about a dog?

418
00:20:54.837 --> 00:20:57.674
This how they policed
up in Boston?

419
00:20:59.133 --> 00:21:02.095
Don't make me come back
and cite you. sir.

420
00:21:03.513 --> 00:21:05.181
Reacher. come on.

421
00:21:47.515 --> 00:21:49.475
Not a single security camera.

422
00:21:52.979 --> 00:21:56.149
Maybe Kliner doesn't want a
record of what's going on here.

423
00:21:56.232 --> 00:21:59.068
Captain Finlay. over here.

424
00:22:01.946 --> 00:22:04.824
Right this way.
Mr. Kliner's expecting you.

425
00:22:06.743 --> 00:22:10.121
That was a hell of a lot
of animal feed back there.

426
00:22:10.204 --> 00:22:13.624
It's the South.
They all have got cows.

427
00:22:19.756 --> 00:22:21.466
I'll do the talking.

428
00:22:21.549 --> 00:22:23.926
Good. I don't like talking.

429
00:22:28.681 --> 00:22:31.350
A family of skilled marksmen.

430
00:22:31.434 --> 00:22:34.187
Uh. just up here. gentlemen.

431
00:22:39.734 --> 00:22:41.652
I'm not sure I can help you.

432
00:22:41.736 --> 00:22:44.030
I wish I could. but all I know
about these killings

433
00:22:44.113 --> 00:22:45.531
is the gossip from the diner.

434
00:22:45.615 --> 00:22:48.284
which we both know is
far from reliable.

435
00:22:49.285 --> 00:22:51.829
Tanner Spivey.
and has himself disappeared.

436
00:22:51.913 --> 00:22:55.708
called your company multiple
times in the last three days.

437
00:22:55.792 --> 00:22:57.919
Pete Jobling. also deceased.

438
00:22:58.002 --> 00:23:00.630
is a former truck driver
for Kliner Industries.

439
00:23:00.713 --> 00:23:02.757
For a company
we contracted with.

440
00:23:02.840 --> 00:23:04.258
Be that as it may.

441
00:23:04.342 --> 00:23:07.970
you paid his legal fees for
a minor traffic violation

442
00:23:08.054 --> 00:23:09.472
that escalated into
disorderly conduct.

443
00:23:09.555 --> 00:23:11.140
We're just looking
for some clarification

444
00:23:11.224 --> 00:23:15.228
as to your relationship with
these men. if you wouldn't mind.

445
00:23:15.311 --> 00:23:18.272
No. Um...

446
00:23:18.356 --> 00:23:20.733
regarding Mr. Jobling.

447
00:23:20.817 --> 00:23:23.611
I ship product
all over the country.

448
00:23:23.694 --> 00:23:25.947
Truck drivers drive too fast.

449
00:23:26.030 --> 00:23:28.741
They get all amped up
on energy drinks.

450
00:23:28.825 --> 00:23:30.993
It behooves me
to keep lawyers on retainer

451
00:23:31.077 --> 00:23:33.454
to get my drivers back on
the road and keep the wheels

452
00:23:33.538 --> 00:23:36.499
of business literally in motion.

453
00:23:36.582 --> 00:23:39.210
And as for Mr. Spivey.
you said he called my company?

454
00:23:39.293 --> 00:23:42.713
We have a general number with
over a dozen departments.

455
00:23:42.797 --> 00:23:46.509
Perhaps Mr. Spivey has a buddy
on the loading docks?

456
00:23:46.592 --> 00:23:49.679
Maybe they were just making
plans to grab a beer after work.

457
00:23:49.762 --> 00:23:54.559
Perhaps. Or perhaps he was
calling for another reason.

458
00:23:54.642 --> 00:23:57.436
I know you're only
doing your job.

459
00:23:57.520 --> 00:23:59.564
and I know you're just trying
to get answers

460
00:23:59.647 --> 00:24:02.441
about your brother's death.

461
00:24:02.525 --> 00:24:04.902
But. if I may speak frankly.

462
00:24:04.986 --> 00:24:07.196
after all I've done
for this town.

463
00:24:07.280 --> 00:24:08.990
after all I've invested into it.

464
00:24:09.073 --> 00:24:11.826
I'm a little insulted
to be under suspicion.

465
00:24:11.909 --> 00:24:13.161
More than a little.

466
00:24:13.244 --> 00:24:16.330
My intention was never
to insult you. Mr. Kliner.

467
00:24:16.414 --> 00:24:18.499
That's okay.

468
00:24:21.377 --> 00:24:24.672
I know you've been under
a lot of stress with

469
00:24:24.755 --> 00:24:26.757
- all that's been happening.
- My intention

470
00:24:26.841 --> 00:24:28.968
is to conduct my investigation
in any manner

471
00:24:29.051 --> 00:24:30.178
I see fit.

472
00:24:30.261 --> 00:24:31.804
And right now.
that means finding out

473
00:24:31.888 --> 00:24:33.806
what you may or may not know.

474
00:24:35.141 --> 00:24:39.312
I know you've had some trouble
settling in here. Captain.

475
00:24:39.395 --> 00:24:42.481
I wonder why that is.

476
00:24:42.565 --> 00:24:45.109
Maybe it's because you're
a Northerner.

477
00:24:45.193 --> 00:24:48.362
Or maybe it's your
fancy education.

478
00:24:49.447 --> 00:24:52.491
Or maybe it's another reason.
Hmm?

479
00:24:55.453 --> 00:24:59.081
Anyway. you haven't exactly
ingratiated yourself

480
00:24:59.165 --> 00:25:03.711
to the good folks of Margrave.

481
00:25:03.794 --> 00:25:05.963
I mean. the people of this town.

482
00:25:06.047 --> 00:25:07.924
the other members of
the police department

483
00:25:08.007 --> 00:25:10.092
want to help you;
they want to work with you.

484
00:25:10.176 --> 00:25:11.719
They've told me so themselves.

485
00:25:11.802 --> 00:25:15.139
We all want justice to be done.

486
00:25:15.223 --> 00:25:18.434
But not if you're
chasing down theories

487
00:25:18.517 --> 00:25:21.395
without any basis in fact.

488
00:25:21.479 --> 00:25:23.689
Some friendly advice?

489
00:25:23.773 --> 00:25:26.400
This evidence trail
you're following?

490
00:25:26.484 --> 00:25:30.279
It's a waste of time
for you and for me.

491
00:25:32.865 --> 00:25:34.617
Leave it.

492
00:25:39.664 --> 00:25:41.749
Horatio Finlay.

493
00:25:42.792 --> 00:25:44.126
Excuse me?

494
00:25:45.962 --> 00:25:47.797
My father's name.

495
00:25:47.880 --> 00:25:50.132
Horatio Finlay.

496
00:25:50.216 --> 00:25:54.178
You might think you're
everybody's daddy in this town.

497
00:25:54.262 --> 00:25:56.931
but you're not mine.

498
00:25:57.014 --> 00:26:00.309
You don't tell me what leads
to chase and how to chase them.

499
00:26:00.393 --> 00:26:04.981
So if I may give you
some friendly advice:

500
00:26:05.064 --> 00:26:07.733
if you keep talking to the cops
on my force.

501
00:26:07.817 --> 00:26:12.488
hinder this investigation
in any way. I will put

502
00:26:12.571 --> 00:26:14.323
my fucking foot
up your fucking ass

503
00:26:14.407 --> 00:26:17.118
until your heart fucking stops.

504
00:26:22.456 --> 00:26:26.252
I think it's time
for you gentlemen to leave.

505
00:26:39.682 --> 00:26:42.018
You know. cursing is a sign

506
00:26:42.101 --> 00:26:45.104
of weak mind
and weaker character.

507
00:26:45.187 --> 00:26:46.564
Shut up.

508
00:26:53.946 --> 00:26:55.489
"You're not my daddy.

509
00:26:55.573 --> 00:26:58.409
Horatio Finlay's my daddy."

510
00:27:01.871 --> 00:27:03.664
Oh. loosen up.

511
00:27:04.915 --> 00:27:07.293
You did the right thing.

512
00:27:07.376 --> 00:27:10.171
Kliner's a bully.

513
00:27:10.254 --> 00:27:13.341
Bullies need to know
they can be punished. too.

514
00:27:16.385 --> 00:27:19.138
Don't cry.
no matter what.

515
00:27:21.932 --> 00:27:24.310
Don't cry. I don't care how
scared or upset you get.

516
00:27:24.393 --> 00:27:26.604
don't you dare let 'em
see you cry.

517
00:27:30.733 --> 00:27:32.735
Boys...

518
00:27:34.236 --> 00:27:36.906
I'm gonna get right to it.

519
00:27:36.989 --> 00:27:39.325
We just came from the hospital.

520
00:27:39.408 --> 00:27:42.661
Curtis Bishop had his face
bashed in with this.

521
00:27:42.745 --> 00:27:44.830
His cheekbone was fractured.

522
00:27:44.914 --> 00:27:46.999
He had to have surgery. sutures.

523
00:27:47.083 --> 00:27:49.668
This is a very serious crime.

524
00:27:49.752 --> 00:27:52.463
There were bicycle tracks
leaving Curtis's house.

525
00:27:52.546 --> 00:27:54.173
You know where they led?

526
00:27:54.256 --> 00:27:57.385
Right there.
To your bike. Joe.

527
00:27:59.845 --> 00:28:01.847
Joe. did you do this?

528
00:28:13.901 --> 00:28:16.362
"All signs indicate yes."

529
00:28:25.913 --> 00:28:28.582
You're not safe at home anymore.

530
00:28:28.666 --> 00:28:31.127
You need to pack a bag
and bounce around motels

531
00:28:31.210 --> 00:28:33.796
- outside Margrave for a while.
- I'm chief detective.

532
00:28:33.879 --> 00:28:35.589
And Morrison was chief
of police. and his balls

533
00:28:35.673 --> 00:28:37.133
are in his stomach now.

534
00:28:37.216 --> 00:28:39.218
Kliner knows you suspect him.

535
00:28:39.301 --> 00:28:40.970
We don't know who to trust
at the station.

536
00:28:41.053 --> 00:28:43.639
Motels. Cash. Fake names.

537
00:28:43.722 --> 00:28:45.975
Travel light.

538
00:28:46.058 --> 00:28:47.518
You mean live like you?

539
00:28:50.521 --> 00:28:52.606
You get used to it.

540
00:29:09.665 --> 00:29:11.125
He's in the back.

541
00:29:11.208 --> 00:29:13.210
What's he doing.
packing his tweed pajamas?

542
00:29:13.294 --> 00:29:16.464
- Probably.
- Jesus.

543
00:29:16.547 --> 00:29:17.798
I don't know what's
more depressing.

544
00:29:17.882 --> 00:29:19.717
this or Morrison's place.

545
00:29:19.800 --> 00:29:22.428
You said your family used
to be in farming. right?

546
00:29:22.511 --> 00:29:23.721
Yeah.

547
00:29:23.804 --> 00:29:25.306
How many head of cattle
can a moving truck

548
00:29:25.389 --> 00:29:27.016
full of animal feed
take care of?

549
00:29:27.099 --> 00:29:29.185
A lot. Why?

550
00:29:29.268 --> 00:29:31.854
How many head of cattle does
Kliner have on his compound?

551
00:29:31.937 --> 00:29:33.522
I don't know.

552
00:29:33.606 --> 00:29:35.191
Uh. I see 'em when I
drive by his north acreage;

553
00:29:35.274 --> 00:29:36.400
call it a hundred.

554
00:29:36.484 --> 00:29:37.818
Nothing for the size
of the land.

555
00:29:37.902 --> 00:29:40.029
I'm gonna ask you again. Why?

556
00:29:40.112 --> 00:29:41.739
I don't know.

557
00:29:41.822 --> 00:29:43.699
He was getting a ton of feed
delivered today.

558
00:29:43.782 --> 00:29:45.242
Organized operation.

559
00:29:45.326 --> 00:29:46.952
Didn't seem like the first time
they were doing it.

560
00:29:47.036 --> 00:29:49.413
It's not like he's running
a commercial farm.

561
00:29:49.497 --> 00:29:52.041
It's Georgia.
Lot of folks have cows.

562
00:29:52.124 --> 00:29:54.251
That's what I hear.

563
00:29:54.335 --> 00:29:57.296
Hey. You been here a year?

564
00:29:57.379 --> 00:29:59.381
Who's your decorator. this guy?

565
00:30:01.383 --> 00:30:03.344
Haven't had time to
furniture shop.

566
00:30:03.427 --> 00:30:05.471
- We good to go?
- Yeah.

567
00:30:05.554 --> 00:30:07.389
There's a motel right outside
Hickory where

568
00:30:07.473 --> 00:30:10.684
we can stay under the radar;
third exit off 85.

569
00:30:10.768 --> 00:30:12.770
Reacher.

570
00:30:12.853 --> 00:30:15.105
I just want to make sure
we're on the same page

571
00:30:15.189 --> 00:30:18.317
because your punch-to-syllable
ratio is about 1:1.

572
00:30:18.400 --> 00:30:19.818
I'm gonna go get a snack.

573
00:30:19.902 --> 00:30:21.320
Just because
it looks like Kliner

574
00:30:21.403 --> 00:30:23.739
might be a part of all this
does not mean you can just

575
00:30:23.822 --> 00:30:24.823
go take him out.

576
00:30:24.907 --> 00:30:26.242
No problem.

577
00:30:26.325 --> 00:30:27.952
- Really?
- A federal agent.

578
00:30:28.035 --> 00:30:30.287
a cop and multiple
civilians are dead.

579
00:30:30.371 --> 00:30:31.664
We're not dealing with
a small-scale operation.

580
00:30:31.747 --> 00:30:32.998
this thing's a hydra;

581
00:30:33.082 --> 00:30:35.042
I cut off one head.
two more grow in its place.

582
00:30:35.125 --> 00:30:37.253
There's no justice
for Joe in that.

583
00:30:37.336 --> 00:30:39.296
I'm gonna uncover
this whole operation.

584
00:30:39.380 --> 00:30:41.131
and then burn it to the ground.

585
00:30:41.215 --> 00:30:42.383
That takes time.
which is something

586
00:30:42.466 --> 00:30:44.468
I have in great quantity.

587
00:30:44.552 --> 00:30:47.930
Taking Kliner out's
the last move. not the first.

588
00:30:48.013 --> 00:30:49.598
I'll pretend I didn't hear that.

589
00:30:49.682 --> 00:30:50.766
Pretend whatever you want.

590
00:30:50.849 --> 00:30:52.017
Okay.

591
00:30:52.101 --> 00:30:54.228
So. we have three
viable leads right now:

592
00:30:54.311 --> 00:30:56.355
Hubble. Jobling and Spivey.

593
00:30:56.438 --> 00:30:58.732
Spivey's in the wind. Hubble's
wife doesn't know anything.

594
00:30:58.816 --> 00:31:00.359
But maybe Jobling's wife does.

595
00:31:00.442 --> 00:31:02.987
It's late. but I can
question her tomorrow.

596
00:31:03.070 --> 00:31:05.155
Do whatever you want.
but Spivey's the answer.

597
00:31:05.239 --> 00:31:07.032
I get him to rat on whoever
paid him to kill Hubble.

598
00:31:07.116 --> 00:31:09.118
we know everything.
I'm finding him.

599
00:31:09.201 --> 00:31:10.286
Now?

600
00:31:10.369 --> 00:31:11.453
He could've told me to
meet him anywhere.

601
00:31:11.537 --> 00:31:12.746
He picked the Blue Cat.

602
00:31:12.830 --> 00:31:13.872
A place he was comfortable.

603
00:31:13.956 --> 00:31:15.624
was probably a regular.

604
00:31:15.708 --> 00:31:18.043
Maybe some of the other regulars
know where he's hiding.

605
00:31:18.127 --> 00:31:20.588
And neither of you
are coming with me.

606
00:31:20.671 --> 00:31:22.965
You'll be made instantly.
You both reek of cop.

607
00:31:23.048 --> 00:31:24.216
I'll meet you in Hickory.

608
00:31:24.300 --> 00:31:26.260
All right.
I'll meet you there. too.

609
00:31:26.343 --> 00:31:28.846
I gotta go get some toothpaste
and deodorant and stuff.

610
00:31:28.929 --> 00:31:31.223
I don't know how
he lives like this.

611
00:31:31.307 --> 00:31:34.184
Yeah. I gotta
make a stop. too. Roscoe?

612
00:31:36.979 --> 00:31:38.147
Be safe.

613
00:31:38.230 --> 00:31:40.774
Oh. watch out.
Keep bein' nice like that

614
00:31:40.858 --> 00:31:43.694
and you're gonna be making
friends around here in no time.

615
00:31:55.331 --> 00:31:56.874
Get off my truck.

616
00:31:57.916 --> 00:32:00.794
You been with that Reacher guy
a lot lately.

617
00:32:00.878 --> 00:32:03.172
Did he tell you
all about himself?

618
00:32:03.255 --> 00:32:06.133
Or is there not much talking
going on?

619
00:32:06.216 --> 00:32:09.219
Your mama teach you the way to
a girl's heart is stalking her?

620
00:32:09.303 --> 00:32:10.971
I wouldn't have to
resort to this

621
00:32:11.055 --> 00:32:12.473
if you would ever
go out with me.

622
00:32:12.556 --> 00:32:15.267
But some outlier strolls in.

623
00:32:15.351 --> 00:32:18.062
next thing I hear.
you guys are best pals.

624
00:32:18.145 --> 00:32:20.981
Five years ago the Kliners
were outliers. Now move.

625
00:32:22.107 --> 00:32:23.525
If you guys are so close.
he must've told you

626
00:32:23.609 --> 00:32:24.985
about Baghdad. right?

627
00:32:25.069 --> 00:32:26.862
'Bout those civilians
that he killed.

628
00:32:28.113 --> 00:32:29.948
And how his connections
got him off?

629
00:32:30.032 --> 00:32:31.450
The charges disappeared.

630
00:32:31.533 --> 00:32:34.036
but nothing goes away
completely. not these days.

631
00:32:34.119 --> 00:32:36.580
Jack Reacher's a murderer.

632
00:32:38.415 --> 00:32:40.125
If you don't let me
into my truck right now.

633
00:32:40.209 --> 00:32:42.586
I'm gonna have you facedown
on the hood in handcuffs.

634
00:32:44.838 --> 00:32:46.548
Maybe I'd like that.

635
00:32:58.435 --> 00:33:00.771
Hey.

636
00:33:00.854 --> 00:33:04.316
I'm looking out for you. Roscoe.
I care about you.

637
00:33:26.046 --> 00:33:27.631
Whoa.

638
00:33:29.174 --> 00:33:30.509
Pull!

639
00:33:31.885 --> 00:33:34.179
Yow! There she is.

640
00:33:34.263 --> 00:33:36.181
Nice shot.

641
00:33:36.265 --> 00:33:39.184
Damn right. I'm bustin' up more
clay than a Tuscan earthquake.

642
00:33:39.268 --> 00:33:42.521
- I'm Steve Williams.
- Oh.

643
00:33:42.604 --> 00:33:45.149
And I gotta tell you.
you guys put on a better party

644
00:33:45.232 --> 00:33:46.567
than the Charleston branch.

645
00:33:46.650 --> 00:33:48.026
Debbie Shane.

646
00:33:48.110 --> 00:33:49.945
- You're from Charleston?
- Mm-hmm.

647
00:33:50.028 --> 00:33:52.072
How's that son of a gun
Tom Sloane doin'?

648
00:33:52.156 --> 00:33:54.491
Still a son of a gun.
in every way possible.

649
00:33:54.575 --> 00:33:55.784
Yeah.

650
00:33:55.868 --> 00:33:57.911
that doesn't surprise me. Pull!

651
00:34:00.539 --> 00:34:02.249
That is how you do it.

652
00:34:02.332 --> 00:34:04.293
Remind me to never get
on your bad side.

653
00:34:04.376 --> 00:34:07.588
So. what're you
doing in Atlanta. Steve?

654
00:34:07.671 --> 00:34:09.465
Uh. grandmother passed.

655
00:34:09.548 --> 00:34:10.883
Oh.

656
00:34:10.966 --> 00:34:12.426
In between wakes I still need
to get some work done.

657
00:34:12.509 --> 00:34:14.386
so I was gonna use your office;
but when I called...

658
00:34:14.470 --> 00:34:16.346
- Excuse me. sir. care for a drink?
- ...they said you closed shop

659
00:34:16.430 --> 00:34:18.974
- early for this event. so here I am.
- Pull!

660
00:34:20.350 --> 00:34:22.060
I'm sorry about your grandma.

661
00:34:22.144 --> 00:34:23.812
but you know what helps
clear your head?

662
00:34:23.896 --> 00:34:25.105
- Shooting things.
- Ah.

663
00:34:25.189 --> 00:34:27.149
Guns make me nervous.

664
00:34:27.232 --> 00:34:29.443
But you know what
you could do for me?

665
00:34:29.526 --> 00:34:32.321
Is tell me a bit about Axis
in Atlanta.

666
00:34:32.404 --> 00:34:34.656
Past few days has me thinking
how life's short.

667
00:34:34.740 --> 00:34:38.744
maybe it's time I shake things
up a bit. transfer offices.

668
00:34:38.827 --> 00:34:40.037
Well. it's a great
place to work.

669
00:34:40.120 --> 00:34:42.623
Nice people.
What division are you in?

670
00:34:42.706 --> 00:34:43.957
Account services.

671
00:34:44.041 --> 00:34:45.959
But truth be told.
I started out wanting to work

672
00:34:46.043 --> 00:34:47.294
in currency management.

673
00:34:47.377 --> 00:34:48.921
Was hoping to make a run
at that again.

674
00:34:49.004 --> 00:34:51.507
Well. that's gonna be tough
to do at our branch. Stevie.

675
00:34:51.590 --> 00:34:53.008
We had a guy
handling that for us.

676
00:34:53.091 --> 00:34:54.802
but he picked up and left
about a year ago

677
00:34:54.885 --> 00:34:57.346
and we discontinued
the department.

678
00:34:57.429 --> 00:34:58.430
It's kind of niche. you know?

679
00:34:58.514 --> 00:34:59.973
Not that many people do it so...

680
00:35:00.057 --> 00:35:01.558
I'm confused.

681
00:35:01.642 --> 00:35:04.186
Your currency manager. what
did you say his name was again?

682
00:35:04.269 --> 00:35:07.773
I didn't.
But it was Paul Hubble.

683
00:35:07.856 --> 00:35:10.692
So this Hubble guy quit
the bank a year ago?

684
00:35:10.776 --> 00:35:13.529
Yep. Up and left without so much
as two weeks' notice.

685
00:35:13.612 --> 00:35:16.073
Kind of a dick move
if you ask me.

686
00:35:16.156 --> 00:35:19.451
Bottom line. we don't really
do the currency thing anymore.

687
00:35:19.535 --> 00:35:21.161
Pull!

688
00:35:25.874 --> 00:35:27.876
Be careful.

689
00:35:27.960 --> 00:35:31.338
A wedding ring falls on the
ground. it's up for grabs.

690
00:35:31.421 --> 00:35:32.673
Really? Says who?

691
00:35:32.756 --> 00:35:34.216
The law.

692
00:35:34.299 --> 00:35:35.634
Famous case of
Finders v. Keepers.

693
00:35:35.717 --> 00:35:37.970
Never heard of it?

694
00:35:38.053 --> 00:35:40.013
No. ma'am. I haven't.

695
00:35:40.097 --> 00:35:42.891
You're not from around here.

696
00:35:42.975 --> 00:35:46.937
That "ma'am" sounds way north
of the Mason-Dixon.

697
00:35:47.020 --> 00:35:48.605
Boston.

698
00:35:48.689 --> 00:35:51.024
Oh. no.

699
00:35:51.108 --> 00:35:52.734
Well. I'll stay

700
00:35:52.818 --> 00:35:54.528
if you promise not to bring up
the Patriots.

701
00:35:54.611 --> 00:35:57.948
Still don't know how the Falcons
blew that Super Bowl.

702
00:35:58.031 --> 00:35:59.616
At 28-20.
you kick the field goal.

703
00:35:59.700 --> 00:36:01.869
I said don't bring it up.

704
00:36:01.952 --> 00:36:04.288
Okay. My bad.

705
00:36:08.667 --> 00:36:11.461
So. what do you do?

706
00:36:11.545 --> 00:36:14.506
Uh. nothing important.

707
00:36:14.590 --> 00:36:16.758
Not recently. anyway.

708
00:36:16.842 --> 00:36:21.346
Cryptic. Cryptic is good.

709
00:36:21.430 --> 00:36:25.142
Sorry. I work in
law enforcement.

710
00:36:25.225 --> 00:36:30.230
Wow. And that
brought you... here?

711
00:36:30.314 --> 00:36:34.651
I'm on a case I can't
seem to untangle.

712
00:36:34.735 --> 00:36:36.486
With a rookie I can trust.

713
00:36:36.570 --> 00:36:38.989
and a veteran
who I'm not sure I can.

714
00:36:39.072 --> 00:36:41.199
At least not to do
the smart thing.

715
00:36:41.283 --> 00:36:43.243
What's your gut say?

716
00:36:43.327 --> 00:36:45.412
Get the hell out of Dodge.

717
00:36:45.495 --> 00:36:48.248
So why are you staying?

718
00:36:51.752 --> 00:36:54.838
Because we're the only ones
who want to make things right.

719
00:36:54.922 --> 00:36:57.215
Seems like a good reason.

720
00:37:01.678 --> 00:37:04.431
Are my questions bothering you?

721
00:37:06.141 --> 00:37:11.063
No. I'm just. uh.
not great at conversation.

722
00:37:11.146 --> 00:37:13.899
But here goes.

723
00:37:13.982 --> 00:37:16.318
Where are you from?

724
00:37:16.401 --> 00:37:20.072
I'm from Marietta.
work in cosmetics.

725
00:37:20.155 --> 00:37:24.368
and my instincts are impeccable.

726
00:37:24.451 --> 00:37:27.788
And my instincts tell me
you're a nice guy.

727
00:37:27.871 --> 00:37:30.415
So why don't we find
another bar around here?

728
00:37:30.499 --> 00:37:34.002
One with pool tables
and cheaper drinks.

729
00:37:34.086 --> 00:37:36.171
Maybe even a dark corner
somewhere

730
00:37:36.254 --> 00:37:37.839
and see where the night
takes us?

731
00:37:40.300 --> 00:37:43.136
I'm married. remember?

732
00:37:44.429 --> 00:37:45.639
Me. too.

733
00:37:45.722 --> 00:37:47.557
But when a fella's marriage
is going well.

734
00:37:47.641 --> 00:37:50.936
he doesn't take his ring off for
the world to see in a motel bar.

735
00:37:52.145 --> 00:37:54.815
I'm flattered.

736
00:37:54.898 --> 00:37:57.734
And you're nice. too.

737
00:37:57.818 --> 00:37:59.695
And lovely.

738
00:38:01.446 --> 00:38:03.365
But I'm not your guy.

739
00:38:07.494 --> 00:38:10.622
Okay.

740
00:38:10.706 --> 00:38:13.208
Can't blame a girl for trying.

741
00:38:15.711 --> 00:38:18.380
Good luck. Officer.

742
00:38:56.585 --> 00:38:58.086
Two-dollar bill?

743
00:38:58.170 --> 00:38:59.504
Huh?

744
00:38:59.588 --> 00:39:00.964
Mailmen have 'em
'cause the Treasury

745
00:39:01.048 --> 00:39:02.924
pawns 'em off on
the Post Office.

746
00:39:03.008 --> 00:39:04.843
Public doesn't like 'em.

747
00:39:04.926 --> 00:39:07.054
Gambling addicts get 'em
in change at the race track

748
00:39:07.137 --> 00:39:08.972
on account of the standard
two-dollar bet.

749
00:39:09.056 --> 00:39:10.849
I don't see a mailbag.

750
00:39:10.932 --> 00:39:12.434
Something tells me you wager
more than you make

751
00:39:12.517 --> 00:39:13.769
and you could use
some extra cash.

752
00:39:13.852 --> 00:39:16.438
Guilty as charged.

753
00:39:18.607 --> 00:39:22.778
You know Tanner Spivey?
He was a regular here.

754
00:39:22.861 --> 00:39:25.781
He's not gonna
tell you anything.

755
00:39:25.864 --> 00:39:27.699
Spivey's a friend.

756
00:39:27.783 --> 00:39:30.160
And he don't need anyone
asking about his business.

757
00:39:30.243 --> 00:39:33.163
Find yourself another bar.

758
00:39:33.246 --> 00:39:37.250
Boxer. Southpaw.

759
00:39:37.334 --> 00:39:38.460
Golden Gloves.

760
00:39:38.543 --> 00:39:42.506
You know. the thing about
boxing: too many rules.

761
00:39:48.887 --> 00:39:49.971
Where's Spivey?

762
00:39:50.055 --> 00:39:52.682
He left town
with some Spanish guys.

763
00:39:52.766 --> 00:39:55.894
Real fast. That's all I know.

764
00:41:26.193 --> 00:41:27.611
Here we go.

765
00:41:27.694 --> 00:41:30.197
Come on.

766
00:41:40.707 --> 00:41:42.834
There you go. stay close.

767
00:41:42.918 --> 00:41:44.502
But not too close.

768
00:41:49.716 --> 00:41:51.718
There you go.

769
00:41:51.801 --> 00:41:53.470
Stay with me. boys.

770
00:42:00.060 --> 00:42:02.479
He went off-road. To the right.

771
00:42:35.887 --> 00:42:38.390
Up ahead. to the right.

772
00:44:26.164 --> 00:44:28.208
